text: Ștefan Iancu (born 26 December 1997) is a Romanian actor. Born in Bucharest, Romania, Iancu began acting at the age of 4. He has remained active throughout much of his childhood and into adult life. ==Education== Iancu is currently a student at the Caragiale Academy of Theatrical Arts and Cinematography. ==Awards== He starred in the 2017 feature film One Step Behind the Seraphim, for which he won a Gopo Award. He received the Best Newcomer award at the 2019 Subtitle Film Festival. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:People from Bucharest Category:21st-century Romanian actors Category:Romanian male film actors Category:Romanian television actors
